@page "/"

<h3>Async Validation Demo — Blazor Web App</h3>
<p>
    This app mirrors the 4 API proposal scenarios from the console samples, then adds dedicated
    infrastructure-failure and cancellation demos.
</p>
<p>
    Each page manually runs <code>Validator.TryValidateObjectAsync</code>, pushes results into a
    <code>ValidationMessageStore</code>, and updates the current <code>EditContext</code>.
</p>

<div class="list-group">
    <a href="/scenario1" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 1:</strong> <code>User</code> — basic async property validation
    </a>
    <a href="/scenario2" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 2:</strong> <code>Order</code> — <code>IValidatableObject</code> + async attributes
    </a>
    <a href="/scenario3" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 3:</strong> <code>MoneyTransfer</code> — <code>IAsyncValidatableObject</code>
    </a>
    <a href="/scenario4" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Scenario 4:</strong> <code>Event</code> — <code>AsyncDateRangeValid</code>
    </a>
    <a href="/error-handling" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Error handling:</strong> DI-backed infrastructure failure demo
    </a>
    <a href="/cancellation" class="list-group-item list-group-item-action">
        <strong>Cancellation:</strong> <code>MoneyTransfer</code> validation with <code>CancellationToken</code> propagation
    </a>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-success mt-3">
    <strong>Manual Blazor pattern:</strong> <code>Validator.TryValidateObjectAsync(..., cancellationToken)</code>
    + <code>ValidationMessageStore</code>.
</div>
